To clean up your CSS for better readability and maintainability, you can make the following changes:

1. **Standardize Units:** Ensure that all dimensions have units specified (e.g., `px` for pixels).

2. **Remove Duplicate Properties:** Remove redundant or overridden properties.

3. **Consistent Indentation:** Use consistent indentation for better readability.

4. **Comment Sections:** Use comments to separate logical sections.

Here is a cleaned-up version:

```css
/* Host Container */
host {
  min-width: 150px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  flex-direction: column;
}

/* Header Styles */
.header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
}

.header-icon {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  margin-right: 8px;
  margin-top: -13px;
  color: var(--mat-sys-on-surface);
}

.header-title {
  font: var(--mat-sys-title-medium);
  font-family: Inter;
  font-weight: 500;
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 180%;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  color: var(--mat-sys-on-surface);
}

.header-subtitle {
  font: var(--mat-sys-title-small);
  font-family: Inter;
  font-weight: 300;
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 24px;
  color: var(--mat-sys-on-surface-variant);
}

/* Status Section */
.status {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  width: 185px;
  height: 40px;
  padding: 0 24px;
  gap: 8px;
  color: #ffffff;
  text-align: center;
}

.status-power,
.status-max-load {
  width: 40px;
  height: 40px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 0 8px;
  background: var(--Base-colors-Gray-400, #a7a7a7);
}

.status-row {
  display: inline-flex;
}

/* Alerts Section */
.alerts {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 70%;
  height: 40px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 8px;
  margin-top: 8px;
  color: #ffffff;
  cursor: pointer;
  background: var(--Base-colors-Main-orange, #ef942f);
}

mat-icon {
  font-size: 12px;
  margin-right: -12px;
  margin-bottom: -12px;
  margin-left: 2px;
}

/* Divider */
mat-divider {
  width: 100%;
  margin: 6px 0;
  border-color: var(--mat-sys-tertiary-fixed-dim);
}

/* Content Section */
.content {
  flex: 1;
  width: 100%;
  display: grid;
}

.content-item {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: 4px 0;
  width: 197px;
  height: 20px;
  gap: 6px;
  color: var(--mat-sys-on-surface);
}

.content-item-label {
  font: var(--mat-sys-label-large);
  font-weight: 700;
}

.content-item-value {
  font: var(--mat-sys-label-large);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

/* Footer Section */
.footer {
  cursor: pointer;
  width: 172px;
  height: 40px;
  min-width: 120px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 8px 12px;
  gap: 8px;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  color: var(--Base-colors-Gray-700, #686868);
  font-size: 18px;
}

mat-icon {
  font-size: 18px;
  margin-bottom: -8px;
  margin-right: -5px;
  margin-left: -3px;
}
```

**Key Adjustments:**
- Ensured that dimensions have units (`px`).
- Consolidated duplicate properties where possible.
- Applied consistent spacing and indentation.
- Improved comments for better section separation.

